cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

This paper proposes a new method for pattern recognition tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, it focuses on improving the performance of extreme learning machines (ELMs), which is a type of neural network. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also includes experiments on image classification, which suggests a possible fit for cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between generalization ability and real-time response, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
